statement.p:
Let S(t) be the number of people who have acquired the virus t days after the ship has left port.  It turns out that a logistic function is a good model for S, and thus we assume that 

  S(t) = \frac{A}{1 + Me^{-kt}}

for some positive constants A, M, and k.  Suppose that after 1 day, 20 people have gotten the virus.
